        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 1:08PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 108 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Deadmans Basin Reservoir, or 25 miles southeast of
Harlowton, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ryegate, Deadmans Basin Reservoir and Shawmut.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
